00:39:28.302 --> 00:39:29.135
She's a her stylist.

00:39:29.135 --> 00:39:32.090
She really likes to get all
this stuff over the internet,

00:39:32.090 --> 00:39:35.510
but that last mile, if
you can get the driver out

00:39:35.510 --> 00:39:38.250
of the local delivery system,
whether it's with drones or you

00:39:38.250 --> 00:39:38.750
name it.

00:39:38.750 --> 00:39:41.040
So a wide range of use cases.

00:39:41.040 --> 00:39:43.660
How are you going to
brand that is important.

00:39:43.660 --> 00:39:45.710
What are the experiences
you're going to deliver?

00:39:45.710 --> 00:39:48.510
It's not just going
from point A to point B

00:39:48.510 --> 00:39:49.820
and getting there safely.

00:39:49.820 --> 00:39:52.120
It's does it pick me up
at my precise location,

00:39:52.120 --> 00:39:55.592
drop me off precisely,
is the ride so nice

00:39:55.592 --> 00:39:57.050
that when I get
out of the vehicle,

00:39:57.050 --> 00:39:59.270
I feel better than
when I got in to it?

00:39:59.270 --> 00:40:02.930
Can I get to more places
with brand A versus brand B?

00:40:02.930 --> 00:40:05.240
That's going to be a
basis of competition.

00:40:05.240 --> 00:40:07.010
But the one place
I think you want

00:40:07.010 --> 00:40:10.900
to be beyond anything else
in this future ecosystem

00:40:10.900 --> 00:40:14.110
is to have the world's best
driver because the world's best

00:40:14.110 --> 00:40:17.320
driver can play on every
one of those use cases.

00:40:17.320 --> 00:40:20.770
And it's typically more
than half the cost per mile

00:40:20.770 --> 00:40:23.020
